Chief (Amb) Michael A. Uba has congratulated the Olu of Warri, Ogiame Atuwatse III on his birthday, praying for his reign to be the best yet in the kingdom. Uba in a signed statement described him as a perfect example of a peace-loving and god-fearing leader. He said the monarch is a role model and shining light of the Iwere people. “I congratulate Your Royal Majesty, Ogiame Atuwatse III, Olu of Warri Kingdom, on this joyous occasion of your 38th birth anniversary. “The Itsekiri people are blessed to have you as the custodian of their culture and tradition and I pray that your reign is filled with successes and prosperity”; it read.